      "id": "d7de7145-6887-ef11-8474-000d3a37e3b6",
      "type": "GeneralText",
      "area": "General",
      "position": 3,
      "content": "The History of Art and Visual Culture (HAVC) program at UC Santa Cruz welcomes transfer students. For the minor, a student may transfer up to three lower-division art history courses taken from other institutions, each satisfying a different geographic regional requirement: Africa and its Diaspora Asia and its Diaspora Europe and the Americas Mediterranean Native Americas Oceania and its Diaspora HAVC 80 – Colonial Histories and Legacies: Africa, Oceania, and the Indigenous Americas* *HAVC 80, or an articulated equivalent, may be used to fulfill a lower-division requirement for one of the following geographic regions: Africa, Native Americas, or Oceania. In the “Preparation for the Minor” section below, you will find lists of courses approved to fulfill these requirements. Petitioning Courses: Transfer students who have completed courses they believe are applicable to the geographic regions listed above, but are not listed in the \"Recommended Preparation\" section below, may petition to have these courses counted toward their HAVC minor requirements. Students should consult the Transfer Credit Petition Process instructions on the HAVC Department website . Please visit the History of Art and Visual Culture website to learn more about this minor. UC Santa Cruz General Catalog: History of Art and Visual Culture Minor Program Statement",
      "contentHtml": "<p><span style=\"font-size: 14px;\">The History of Art and Visual Culture (HAVC) program at UC Santa Cruz welcomes transfer students. For the minor, a student may transfer up to three lower-division art history courses taken from other institutions, each satisfying a different geographic regional requirement: </span></p><p><br></p><ul><li><span style=\"font-size: 14px;\">Africa and its Diaspora</span></li><li><span style=\"font-size: 14px;\">Asia and its Diaspora</span></li><li><span style=\"font-size: 14px;\">Europe and the Americas</span></li><li><span style=\"font-size: 14px;\">Mediterranean</span></li><li><span style=\"font-size: 14px;\">Native Americas</span></li><li><span style=\"font-size: 14px;\">Oceania and its Diaspora</span></li><li><span style=\"font-size: 14px;\">HAVC 80 –&nbsp;Colonial Histories and Legacies: Africa, Oceania, and the Indigenous Americas*</span></li></ul><p class=\"ql-indent-1\"><em style=\"font-size: 12px;\">*HAVC 80, or an articulated equivalent, may be used to fulfill a lower-division requirement for one of the following geographic regions: Africa, Native Americas, or Oceania.</em></p><p><br></p><p><span style=\"font-size: 14px;\">In the “Preparation for the Minor” section below, you will find lists of courses approved to fulfill these requirements.</span></p><p><br></p><p><strong style=\"font-size: 14px;\">Petitioning Courses: </strong><span style=\"font-size: 14px;\">Transfer students who have completed courses they believe are applicable to the geographic regions listed above, but are not listed in the \"Recommended Preparation\" section below, may petition to have these courses counted toward their HAVC minor requirements. Students should consult the </span><a href=\"https://havc.ucsc.edu/academics/undergraduate/transfer-credit/\" rel=\"noopener noreferrer\" target=\"_blank\" style=\"font-size: 14px;\">Transfer Credit Petition Process instructions on the HAVC Department website</a><span style=\"font-size: 14px;\">.</span></p><p><br></p><p><br></p><p><span style=\"font-size: 14px;\">Please visit the </span><a href=\"https://havc.ucsc.edu/\" rel=\"noopener noreferrer\" target=\"_blank\" style=\"font-size: 14px;\">History of Art and Visual Culture website</a><span style=\"font-size: 14px;\"> to learn more about this minor.</span></p><p><a href=\"https://catalog.ucsc.edu/en/current/general-catalog/academic-units/arts-division/history-of-art-and-visual-culture/history-of-art-and-visual-culture-minor/\" rel=\"noopener noreferrer\" target=\"_blank\" style=\"font-size: 14px;\">UC Santa Cruz General Catalog: History of Art and Visual Culture Minor Program Statement</a></p>"
